name: trim-x

1.0.0.name: trim-x
1.0.0.description: This method removes whitespace from the left and right end of a string.

scripts.clean:all: npm run clean:jasmine && npm run clean
scripts.build: npm run clean && npm run lint && npm run browserify && npm run uglify && npm run docs && npm test && npm run security
scripts.build:name: replace-x " @module .*" " @module $(node -p -e "require('./package.json').name")" index.js
scripts.build:replace: npm run build:setver && npm run build:name && npm run build:description
scripts.production: npm run clean:all && npm run build:jasmine && npm run build:replace && npm run build
scripts.docs:name: replace-x "@{PACKAGE-NAME}" "$(node -p -e "require('./package.json').name")" README.md
scripts.docs:badges: ncp badges.html README.md && npm run docs:name
scripts.docs: npm run docs:badges && jsdoc2md --name-format --example-lang js index.js >> README.md

readme: ## trim-x This method removes whitespace from the start and end of a string. ### `module.exports(string)` number ### `trim-x` string This method removes whitespace from the start and end of a string. (ES2019) **Kind**: static property of [trim-x](#module_trim-x) **Returns**: string - The trimmed string. **Throws**: - TypeError If string is null or undefined or not coercible. | Param | Type | Description | | ------ | ------------------- | --------------------------------------- | | string | string | The string to trim the whitespace from. | **Example** ```js import trim from 'trim-x'; console.log(trim(' \t\na \t\n') === 'a'); // true ```
